  "body": "Getting a lot of these errors using golang http client polling geth for getwork and getblockbynumber every 100ms. This is errors from my ether-proxy https://github.com/sammy007/ether-proxy/issues/11 and it worked perfectly for months before i tested it on current develop. Any idea what happened with RPC http code that can cause this?\n\n```\nUnsolicited response received on idle HTTP channel starting with \"HTTP/1.1 200 OK\\r\\nContent-Length: 113\\r\\nContent-Type: application/json\\r\\n\\r\\n{\\\"jsonrpc\\\":\\\"2.0\\\",\\\"error\\\":{\\\"code\\\":-32600,\\\"message\\\":\\\"read tcp 127.0.0.1:8888-\\\\u003e127.0.0.1:60404: i/o timeout\\\"}}\\n\"; err=<nil>\n```\n",
